track_notes:
This approach requires a four-wheel drive truck and involves a short but very steep hill. The track goes all the way to the microwave tower on the summit of the ridge, but access will depend upon snow conditions and the comfort zone of the driver.
The access to the track from the highway is immediately to the west of the bridge crossing the railway line
track_title: From the west avoiding private land and locked gates

track_notes: Park in or near the rest area just in BC. Take the power line acces east until you hit a track, then north a short distance. The east along the pipeline access track to a vehicle track that is posted no motorized vehicles. Folow this a short ditance until the y junction, go left until you find the pipeline track again. Go right and up the pipeline track until you hit the top of the ridge, go right. A short easy bushwhack up hill until you find the access road, follow to the top.
track_title: Hiking track from the rest area to the west
